FBIS4-59907 "drnes097_p_94001" FBIS-NES-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Mazar-e Sharif Airport Forced To Shut Down Mazar-e Sharif Airport Forced To Shut Down LD1805163994 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 18 May 94 LD1805163994 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text] Mazar-e Sharif Airport cannot be used for flights. Bakhtar has received reports from Mazar-e Sharif that during recent days the airport, from where aircraft of the infamous militias [word indistinct], has been under heavy weapon fire by Mojahedin and forces of the Islamic Army. This airport has been put out of operation completely.
